  "response": "`.coc/` is untouched. The changes are symmetric across both plugins (5 JSON files each: monsters, poisons, spells, tomes, weapons) plus ref files and scripts. 10 verify scripts total.\n\nThis iteration found and fixed additional issues that the prior run missed:\n\n## Summary of this iteration's additional rigor\n\n**Tomes (deeper coverage)**: The prior run accepted 13 unmatched our-tomes. I manually verified all 13 against the OCR and found:\n- **'unknown'** → was a bad-keyed duplicate of \"Book of Iod\" primary edition. **Renamed to 'ancient tongue unknown'** with display_name for proper verification.\n- 11 edition-style entries (descriptive keys like \"English 1647 Janus Aquaticus\") were verified via a new **edition secondary pass** in the verifier (matching by language/date/author cues).\n- **Mum-Rath Papyri**: documented as OCR-corrupted (merged row, stats unrecoverable) — the one genuinely unverifiable entry.\n- Result: tomes went from 13 unmatched → **0 unmatched** (all 98 verified).\n\n**Monsters (deeper coverage)**: Found that **Mi-Go**'s stat block heading was in the OCR but missing its `## ` prefix (plain text). Fixed the chunk parser to recognize plain-text stat headings preceding a table. Mi-Go now verified (STR/CON/SIZ/DEX/INT/POW/HP all match, attack 1D6 matches). Also fixed the attack ahead-scan to stop at other monsters' prose (was misattributing Nightgaunt's 1D4 to Mi-Go). Result: characteristics 32→**33/33**.\n\n**Spells (deeper coverage)**: Found **Wither Limb** (Cost under a `## Cost:` heading) and **Bless Blade** (plain-text name, no `## `) were in the OCR but unmatched. Enhanced the parser to handle both OCR quirks. Result: matched 47→**49**, both cost_mp and cost_sanity 0 mismatches.\n\nThe other tables (weapons, poisons, phobias/manias, occupations, bout, skills) were re-confirmed clean with their unmatched buckets validated as legitimate (natural weapons, OCR-incomplete coverage, formula-based values, OCR-corrupted rows).\n\